            <div id="review_3136686_full_content" class="full-content"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>

      
  



  <div xmlns:v="http://rdf.data-vocabulary.org/#" typeof="v:Review">
    <div class="main review-item" id="2965482">
        

  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/2965482/" class="title-link">参谋，为了战争而生存的怪物！</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-2965482"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/mywildheart/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u1164472-40.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/mywildheart/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">国士</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar50 main-title-rating" title="力荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2010-01-30"
      class="main-meta">2010-01-30 12:37:51</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_2965482_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                           日本是如何走向军国化并在此军国化体制下逐步走向癫狂的？这是战后日本人可能最想知道的问题，也是其最痛苦的思想拷问。日军参谋对战争的推动，是本书新颖的切入点。这个切入点展示特殊的历史及文化所导致的日本军国主义过程，及其对全亚洲人民的造成的巨大的肉体和精...

